history.content:
From your description I think you are a senior and leaning more towards CS. I will encourage you to take EE20. It's a relatively math heavy class compared to the programming classes but it's not that demanding from my experience. As I'm doing ee149 hw, it seems that there is that material from ee20 though it might not be the focus. As a eecs major leaning more towards EE, I think EE20 complements the CS stuff you learnt very well if you can do the work and understand it. 

I'm also taking cs162 and it seems the wait list is pretty long already. Not sure if you can just sign up. My personal advice is to take ee149 and ee20. Trust me, ee20 is not that bad if you put in the work.

This semester, signed up for EE40, EECS149, CS186.

There is a conflict between 149 and 40, and I need EE40 | EE20 to graduate

Here are my two options:

-Switch EE40 for EE20, which would put me in a much more math heavy class.  Definitely out of my comfort zone.  Less passionate about the subject matter.  I love the EE40 topics.

-Switch EECS149 for CS 162 or CS 164, both intense classes but less impacted.

So do I gamble and take EE20, where I'm uncomfortable, or switch 149 and possibly overwhelm myself this semester?
history.subject: EE 40 vs 20
